cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about text classification using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and max pooling. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also discusses the interpretability of the model, which suggests that it may belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper proposes a multi-sentence strategy, which indicates that it may also belong to the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
